<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFJohnson1957" class="citation cs2">Johnson, Paul Bede (1957), <i>The Suez War</i>, London: MacGibbon &amp; Kee</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Suez+War&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=MacGibbon+%26+Kee&amp;rft.date=1957&amp;rft.aulast=Johnson&amp;rft.aufirst=Paul+Bede&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APaul+Johnson+%28writer%29" class="Z3988"></span>.</li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFJohnson1958" class="citation cs2">&#8212;&#8212;&#8212; (1958), <i>Journey into Chaos</i>, Western Policy in the Middle East, London: MacGibbon &amp; Kee</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Journey+into+Chaos&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.series=Western+Policy+in+the+Middle+East&amp;rft.pub=MacGibbon+%26+Kee&amp;rft.date=1958&amp;rft.aulast=Johnson&amp;rft.aufirst=Paul+Bede&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APaul+Johnson+%28writer%29" class="Z3988"></span>.</li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFJohnson1971" class="citation cs2">&#8212;&#8212;&#8212; (1971), <i>Statesmen and Nations</i>, Sidgwick &amp; Jackson</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Statesmen+and+Nations&amp;rft.pub=Sidgwick+%26+Jackson&amp;rft.date=1971&amp;rft.aulast=Johnson&amp;rft.aufirst=Paul+Bede&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APaul+Johnson+%28writer%29" class="Z3988"></span>.  An anthology of <i>New Statesman</i> articles from the 1950s and 1960s.</li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFJohnson1977" class="citation cs2">&#8212;&#8212;&#8212; (1977), <i>Enemies of Society</i>, Weidenfeld &amp; Nicolson</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Enemies+of+Society&amp;rft.pub=Weidenfeld+%26+Nicolson&amp;rft.date=1977&amp;rft.aulast=Johnson&amp;rft.aufirst=Paul+Bede&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APaul+Johnson+%28writer%29" class="Z3988"></span>.</li>
